Sentence: The chef prepared a delicious meal.
The : definite article
chef : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "prepared"
prepared : verb "prepare", past tense, active voice
a : indefinite article
delicious : adjective, descriptive
meal : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "prepared"

Sentence: She loves reading mystery novels.
She : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "loves"
loves : verb "love", third person singular, present tense, active voice
reading : gerund, functions as part of the direct object phrase
mystery : common noun, singular, acting as an adjective
novels : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "loves"

Sentence: David fixed the broken window.
David : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "fixed"
fixed : verb "fix", past tense, active voice
the : definite article
broken : adjective, past participle
window : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "fixed"

Sentence: They invited us to the party.
They : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "invited"
invited : verb "invite", past tense, active voice
us : personal pronoun, first person plural, direct object of the verb "invited"
to : preposition
the : definite article
party : common noun, singular

Sentence: The company launched a new product.
The : definite article
company : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "launched"
launched : verb "launch", past tense, active voice
a : indefinite article
new : adjective, descriptive
product : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "launched"

Sentence: Maria wrote a long letter.
Maria : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "wrote"
wrote : verb "write", past tense, active voice
a : indefinite article
long : adjective, descriptive
letter : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "wrote"

Sentence: He hates waiting in long lines.
He : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "hates"
hates : verb "hate", third person singular, present tense, active voice
waiting : gerund, direct object of the verb "hates"
in : preposition
long : adjective, descriptive
lines : common noun, plural

Sentence: The dog chased the red ball.
The : definite article
dog : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "chased"
chased : verb "chase", past tense, active voice
the : definite article
red : adjective, descriptive
ball : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "chased"

Sentence: We need more time.
We : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "need"
need : verb "need", present tense, active voice
more : determiner, quantifier
time : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "need"

Sentence: The teacher graded the exams quickly.
The : definite article
teacher : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "graded"
graded : verb "grade", past tense, active voice
the : definite article
exams : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "graded"
quickly : adverb, modifies the verb

Sentence: Sarah bought him a gift.
Sarah : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "bought"
bought : verb "buy", past tense, active voice
him : personal pronoun, third person singular, indirect object
a : indefinite article
gift : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "bought"

Sentence: The storm destroyed the old bridge.
The : definite article
storm : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "destroyed"
destroyed : verb "destroy", past tense, active voice
the : definite article
old : adjective, descriptive
bridge : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "destroyed"

Sentence: I enjoy swimming in the ocean.
I : personal pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "enjoy"
enjoy : verb "enjoy", present tense, active voice
swimming : gerund, direct object of the verb "enjoy"
in : preposition
the : definite article
ocean : common noun, singular

Sentence: The mechanic repaired my car.
The : definite article
mechanic : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "repaired"
repaired : verb "repair", past tense, active voice
my : possessive determiner
car : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "repaired"

Sentence: She answered the question correctly.
She : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "answered"
answered : verb "answer", past tense, active voice
the : definite article
question : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "answered"
correctly : adverb, modifies the verb
